r of Tunare's usefulness?</span><hr size=1> Any reason to buy this spell?  Or should I just scribe it if it drops and not worry about it otherwise.  From what I can recall, it is an animal only MR debuff?  Can't imagine that anyone would ever actually memorize something like that, as many animals don't seem to have their animal flag set in the database.  I think that VI might have created it as fodder for the "Druids are Xth best at..." threads.  But then again, what do I know.  Maybe one of you has some reasoning that would inspire me to camp NFP for it.<br>
<br>
"Druids are 9th best at animal debuffing..."<br>
 <p><br>
Sylvus Tyrstalone<br>
53 Druid, Ixtlan<br>
Veeshan</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uligge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ligge</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/23/01 10:06:50 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.eqguide.com/images/vermsmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Glamour of Tunare's usefulness?</span><hr size=1> I have used it in Chardok a few times. Had the extra spell slot so I had it loaded anyway. Root dog, Debuff dog, snare dog, make uber pet :) I kept him probably 30-40 mins one night. Yes that was recasts but snare gave me room to run a bit off from him and do so easily. <p><p><font face="Trebuchet MS, Tahoma" size="1"><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=6031>Ligge</a> - Changing Tide CoGuildleader<br><font color=green><a href="http://pub17.ezboard.com/beqguide">Changing Tide's Boards</a><b> || </b><a href="http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthefolk">The Folk's Boards</a></font><br><b>"You must be the change you wish to see in the world." - Mahatma Ghandi</b><br>"Never argue with an idiot. They drag you down to their level then beat you with experience."</font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubatou062671.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Batou062671</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/23/01 11:49:23 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Glamour of Tunare's usefulness?</span><hr size=1> Aye, I used it last night in sirens grotto to debuff the servant manatees before charming them and I had a pet that lasted a good long while.  Got a bit dicey when charm broke once or twice but other than that it worked really well. <p>Batou Thornhill<BR>
Preserver of the 56th Season<BR>
Harbingers<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uelawnah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elawnah</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://members.tripod.co.uk/redhotant/icons/iconoc11.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/24/01 12:23:39 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://elawnah.homestead.com/files/again....jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Glamour of Tunare's usefulness?</span><hr size=1> In the right situation its useful. <br>
